===Etymology===
{{IPAchar|/opoki/}}<ref>citation needed</ref> → {{IPAchar|/oɸoki/}} → {{IPAchar|/oɸokiki/}} → {{IPAchar|/owokiː/}} → {{IPAchar|/oːkiː/}}

Appears in the {{w|Muromachi period}}, 1337 to 1573 CE.

From older adjectival noun {{ja-r|大き|おおき}}, derived from attributive form ''ōki'' of cognate adjective ''ōshi'' (meaning both “large” or “many”, spelled as {{ja-r|多し|おおし}} or {{ja-r|大し|おおし}}, modern {{cog|ja|-}} {{ja-r|多い|おおい|many}}), in turn derived from {{der|ja|ojp|sort=おおきい|-}} adjectival noun ''opo'' (“indistinct; of uncertain size, shape, or amount”; read as ''ō'' in modern {{cog|ja|-}}, spelled as {{ja-l|凡}} or {{ja-l|大}}).

